OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA few bright or sunny spells
OL,6,Fotherwise rather cloudy. Mainly dry
OL,7,Fwith just a few scattered showers,
OL,8,Fthese mainly affecting coastal Argyll
OL,9,Fand perhaps South Lanarkshire. Lighter
OL,10,Fwinds.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FSome late sunshine then a dry
OL,13,Fnight with some clear periods, though
OL,14,Fperhaps cloudier across eastern
OL,15,FLanarkshire.
OL,16,
OL,17,CSaturday:FA good deal of dry weather
OL,18,Fwith the best of the sunshine towards
OL,19,Fthe west coast. Cloud building inland
OL,20,Fperhaps bringing the odd light shower.
OL,21,FA bit colder.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
